            , one of the partners, stood behind the counter, talking to a lady; I saw the prisoner serve a little boy with some oil; I saw him take the money and put it on the counter - I was called away, but went behind the counter, and as near as I could count the money was 3s. 9d.: Mr. Hope went behind the counter, and while I was serving a customer I saw the prisoner take the money and put it into his own pocket - I told the partner of it directly, but he said nothing about it till the Saturday; this was Thursday evening - he was not at business on Friday: the prisoner was not behind the counter when he received the money: I cannot say he did not afterwards put it into the till - it remained on the counter about five minutes.</p>
